'''Papyrus Oxyrhynchus 299''' ('''P. Oxy. 299''' or '''P. Oxy. II 299''') is a fragment of a Letter concerning a Mouse-Catcher, in [[Greek language|Greek]]. It was discovered in [[Oxyrhynchus]]. The manuscript was written on [[papyrus]] in the form of a sheet. It was written in the late first century. Formerly it was held in the [[Bradfield College]]. The actual owner of the codex and place of its housing is unknown.<ref name = Oxy>[http://163.1.169.40/cgi-bin/library?e=d-000-00---0POxy--00-0-0--0prompt-10---4------0-1l--1-en-50---20-about---00031-001-1-0utfZz-8-00&a=d&c=POxy&cl=CL5.1.2&d=HASH66d3681e4cf54ce692ae08 P. Oxy. 299] at the Oxyrhynchus Online </ref>
== Description == The measurements of the fragment are 54 by 108&nbsp;mm.<ref name = OPII>{{Cite book | last = Grenfell | first = B. P. | authorlink = Bernard Pyne Grenfell | last2 = Hunt | first2 = A. S. | authorlink2 = Arthur Surridge Hunt | title = Oxyrhynchus Papyri II | publisher = Egypt Exploration Fund | year = 1898 | location = London | pages = 300–301 | url = https://archive.org/stream/oxyrhynchuspappt02grenuoft#page/300/mode/2up | doi = | isbn = }}</ref>
The document was written by Horus to Appion about the payment of a mouse-catcher.{{r|Oxy|OPII}} It was published by [[Bernard Pyne Grenfell]] and [[Arthur Surridge Hunt]] in 1899.{{r|Oxy|OPII}}
